  <discussion>Smilax glauca is easily recognized by its glaucous to whitened abaxial leaf
        surfaces, which, however, may be altered by heat in drying. It is reportedly the most weedy
        species of the genus. The plants tend to be evergreen in the more southern part of the
        distribution.</discussion>
